{"cursor":"4661","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":":For the mathematician, [[Robert Remak (mathematician)]] {{Infobox scientist\n|name = |image =Robert Remak.jpg |image_size =210px |caption = |birth_date =\n26 July 1815 = Posen |death_date = 29 August 1865 |death_place = Bad Kissingen\n|residence = |citizenship = |nationality = Polish/German |ethnicity = |field =\nEmbryology Physiologist Neurology |work_institutions = |alma_mater =\nUniversity of Berlin |doctoral_advisor = Ferdinand Georg Frobenius Hermann\nAmandus Schwarz |doctoral_students = |known_for = Ectoderm, mesoderm and\nendoderm |author_abbrev_bot = |author_abbrev_zoo = |influences = |influenced =\n|prizes = |religion = |footnotes = |signature = }} 'Robert Remak' (26 July\n1815 â 29 August 1865) was a Polish/German embryologist, physiologist, and\nneurologist, born in Posen, Prussia. Dr. Remak obtained his medical degree\nfrom Friedrich Wilhelm University in Berlin in 1838 specializing in\nneurology. Kish, B. 1954. Forgotten leaders in modern medicine: Valentin,\nGruby, Remak, Auerbach. Transactions of the American Philosophical Society.\n'44', Issue 2, 139â317. He is best known for reducing Karl Ernst von\nBaer's four germ layers to three: the ectoderm, mesoderm, and endoderm. He\nalso discovered unmyelinated nerve fibres and the nerve cells in the heart\nsometimes called Remak's ganglia. He studied under Johannes Muller at the\nUniversity of Berlin.\n\nRemak discovered that the origin of cells was by the division of pre-existing\ncells. Magner, Lois N. A history of the life sciences. p185\n\nDespite his accomplishments, because of his Jewish faith, he was repeatedly\ndenied full professor status until late in life, and even then was denied the\nusual benefits of the position. Rudolf Virchow, one of the founders of modern\ncell theory, plagiarized the notion that all cells come from pre-existing cells\nfrom Remak.\n\nHis son Ernst Julius Remak was also a neurologist and his grandson was the\nmathematician Robert Remak who died in Auschwitz in 1942.\n","linknr":167,"url":"Robert_Remak","recorded":1376413932,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Robert_Remak&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Robert_Remak&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Remak","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.visualEditor.viewPageTarget.noscript&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Robert_Remak_(mathematician)","/wiki/File:Robert_Remak.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9b/Robert_Remak.jpg/210px-Robert_Remak.jpg","/wiki/Pozna%C5%84","/wiki/Bad_Kissingen","/wiki/Poland","/wiki/Germany","/wiki/Embryology","/wiki/Physiologist","/wiki/Neurology","/wiki/Alma_mater","/wiki/University_of_Berlin","/wiki/Doctoral_advisor","/wiki/Ferdinand_Georg_Frobenius","/wiki/Hermann_Amandus_Schwarz","/wiki/Ectoderm","/wiki/Mesoderm","/wiki/Endoderm","/wiki/Poland","/wiki/Germany","/wiki/Pozna%C5%84","#cite_note-1","/wiki/Karl_Ernst_von_Baer","/wiki/Germ_layer","/wiki/Ectoderm","/wiki/Mesoderm","/wiki/Endoderm","/w/index.php?title=Remak%27s_ganglia&action=edit&redlink=1","/wiki/Johannes_Muller","/wiki/Cell_division","#cite_note-2","#cite_note-